2500|$|Back in 1963, it was {{proposed}} by Winterberg that the ignition of thermonuclear micro-explosions, {{could be achieved}} by an intense beam of microparticles accelerated to a velocity of 1000km/s. And in 1968, [...] Winterberg proposed to use intense electron and ion beams, generated by Marx generators, for the same purpose. Most recently, Winterberg has proposed the ignition of a deuterium microexplosion, with a gigavolt super-Marx generator, which is a <b>Marx</b> <b>Generator</b> driven by up to 100 ordinary Marx generators.|$|E
5000|$|A similar circuit is the <b>Marx</b> <b>generator,</b> {{which has}} the same [...] "ladder" [...] structure, but {{consists}} of resistors, capacitors and spark gaps. The <b>Marx</b> <b>generator</b> produces short pulses, whereas the CW generator produces a constant DC.|$|E
